text: Maira Claro (born 7 March 1995) is a Brazilian volleyball player. She played for the Brazilian women's national volleyball team. She participated at the 2013 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup, 2016 Montreux Volley Masters, 2016 Women's U22 South American Volleyball Championship, 2017 FIVB Volleyball Women's U23 World Championship, and 2019 FIVB Volleyball Women's Nations League. == References == Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Brazilian volleyball players
